<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-03-22T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-03-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">690d.003/20: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-03-22T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 22,
                                        1924—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Before taking action on your telegram of March 20, 11 a.m., concerning
                            increase in customs duty on alcohol, Department desires information
                            regarding provisions of the law in question and the attitude of
                            nationals of other countries.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>